            ["GP6", "GP15", "GP16", null]
        ]
    },
    "$matrix_comment": "Physical GPIO per logical key (Rev A x-monotonic routing remap; ORDER-READINESS.md Layer 4): row 0 SW1-SW4 = GP12,GP9,GP5,GP2 | row 1 SW5-SW8 = GP11,GP8,GP4,GP1 | row 2 SW9-SW12 = GP10,GP7,GP3,GP0. Row 3: [3,0]=SW13 2U (GP6), [3,1]=encoder push ENC_SW (GP15), [3,2]=TTP223 touch OUT (GP16, PCB straps AHLB active-low so it reads like a normal direct pin), [3,3]=unused. Keymaps address [row][col] and are unchanged by the remap. GP18/GP19 (I2C1 to J2), GP20, GP28 and the net named GP21 (silicon GPIO24) are spares on the DNP J2 expansion header and are deliberately unused here.",
    "encoder": {
        "rotary": [
            {"pin_a": "GP13", "pin_b": "GP14"}
        ]
    },
    "$joystick_comment": "PLACEHOLDER calibration - 512 center, 0..1023 span. Real low/rest/high come from the bring-up ADC sweep on the Adafruit 3103 module (meter its pinout before soldering; see the hand-solder afterlist). QMK native output is HID gamepad; arrow/scroll modes are custom code in loudest_micro.c (JS_MODE keycode). JOY_X_ADC = GP26/ADC0, JOY_Y_ADC = GP27/ADC1 per ORDER-READINESS.md Layer 4.",
    "joystick": {
        "driver": "analog",
        "button_count": 0,
        "axes": {
            "x": {"input_pin": "GP26", "low": 0, "rest": 512, "high": 1023},
            "y": {"input_pin": "GP27", "low": 0, "rest": 512, "high": 1023}
        }
    },
    "ws2812": {
